findComplexes

public ArrayList findComplexes(cytoscape.CyNetwork inputNetwork)
Step 2: Find all complexes given a scored graph. If the input network has not been scored, this method will return null.

Parameters:
inputNetwork - - The scored network to find complexes in.
Returns:
An ArrayList containing an ArrayList for each complex. Each complex is stored as a simple list of node IDs of the nodes in the input network that are part of the complex.

scoreComplex

public double scoreComplex(giny.model.GraphPerspective gpComplex)
Score a complex. Currently this ranks larger, denser complexes higher, although in the future other scoring functions could be created

Parameters:
gpComplex - - The GINY GraphPerspective version of the complex
Returns:
The score of the complex

calcDensity

                          boolean includeLoops)
Calculate the density of a network The density is defined as the number of edges/the number of possible edges

Parameters:
gpInputGraph - The input graph to calculate the density of
includeLoops - Include the possibility of loops when determining the number of possible edges.
Returns:
The density of the network

getKCore

public giny.model.GraphPerspective getKCore(giny.model.GraphPerspective gpInputGraph,
                                            int k)
Find a k-core of a network. A k-core is a subgraph of minimum degree k

Parameters:
gpInputGraph - The input network
k - The k of the k-core to find e.g. 4 will find a 4-core
Returns:
Returns a subgraph with the core, if any was found at given k

getHighestKCore

public Object[] getHighestKCore(giny.model.GraphPerspective gpInputGraph)
Find the highest k-core in the input graph.

Parameters:
gpInputGraph - The input network
Returns:
Returns the k-value and the core as an Object array. The first object is the highest k value i.e. objectArray[0] The second object is the highest k-core as a GraphPerspective i.e. objectArray[1]
